            <tr><td colspan="2" class="mhback" align="right"><span class="fs8"><a class="mh" href="/db/classes.html?class=3"><img src="/shared/root_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Up" width="17" height="11" /> Thread Index</a> |  <a class="mh" href="/db/classes.html?class=3;post=1"><img src="/shared/new_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="New" width="17" height="11" /> New Subject</a> | <a class="mh" href="/db/classes.html?class=3;mid=97067092513411;post=1"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply" width="17" height="11" /> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr> <tr><td colspan="2"><table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2"><a name="97067092513411"></a><span class="msgSubject">The Monk and The Art Of Feign Pulling</span><br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: The Monk and The Art Of Feign Pulling";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Oct  4th  2000 at 10:48am EDT<span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=3;mid=97067092513411;post=1;replyto=97067092513411"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    </span></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=634"><span class="Scholar">Altizar</span></a><b><span class="Scholar"><br/>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />104 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=3;mid=97067092513411;page=;howmany=50#97067092513411"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Later in a Monks Life, he becomes the master of a technique called the Feign Death Pull.  This technique is the source of all the monks fabled pulling power. <br /> <br />First off, before the level of 17 where a monk first gets his Fiegn Death skill, Monks are not the best choice to pull for a group.  I wouldn't  consider starting to pulling until the Feign Death skill is over 50, when you can be reasonable sure that it's going to work more often. <br /> <br />Why is the feign pull such a powerful weapon in a groups arsenal?  The biggest reason is because if you get a bad pull, a monk can abort the pull without him or any other group member dieing!!  Second the monk has a pretty good chance to split a spawn with multiple MOBs. <br /> <br />Splitting a multiple spawn is where the art truely becomes apparent in a monk.  Here are some things to keep in mind: <br /> <br />1) a successful split may and probably will take multiple Feigns. <br /> <br />2) when you pull multiples, you want to run a distance away from the spawn point then Feign.  Be sure to use your other camera angles once you feign, that way you can see what the MOBs are doing. <br /> <br />3) On a successful split, Usually the MOBs will wander back to thier spawn points at different times.  What you want to do is to stand up when there is only 1 MOB standing over what he thinks is you corpse.  Hopefully the other spawns are out of aggro range, if they aren't just feign again. <br /> <br />3.5) Never Stand up until Feign Death is rdy to fire again, unless you failed at the initial Feign Death attempt <br /> <br />4) Sometimes the MOB's your trying to split will start to wander back to thier points at the same time, this can't be helped, just let them go back and try to split them again. Sometimes it can take 3-4 attempts, patience is a virtue and extends your life. <br /> <br />5) Always have your group camp a safe distance away.  As a last resort you need room to abort the pull, without any of them being inside the MOB's aggro radius. <br /> <br />6) Remind your group to Never Cast spells on you when you are pulling because it will break your feigns and the MOBS will procede to pummel you. <br /> <br />7) Carry along some Shurikens...These are very handy to pull from a little distance away and give you a head start without the MOB's beating on you immediately. <br /> <br />Warning) Be very careful when trying to split a spawn that includes casters.  If you feign while a caster is in the process casting, once that spell goes off, it will break your feign wether it was successful or not, and all the creatures will continue to beat the snot out of you. <br /> <br />Now that you have One or Two (However many MOBs you're group feels that it can handle) back.  It's time to let the Tank do his job.  But hold on a sec, the MOB is really pissed off at you because you hit it first, and are doing more damage to it than the Tank.  Here is where the second aspect of Fegin Death comes in.  You stop attacking, Feign, and Tada the MOB turns his attention to the Tank.  You stand up and procede to give the MOB a walloping like he's never seen before from the backside.  (One Note: If you are pulling Multiple MOBs be sure that your tank(s) have taken care to aggrevate all the MOB's or the enchanter (god's bless them) have mezed before you Feign, otherwise your casters and Healers might be dead in a very short order.) <br /> <br />While pulling use group talk extensively.  Let the group know what is going on and what to expect when you and your new friends are coming back.  Nothing is really more annoying than having to abort a complicated pull because the group was bored and pulled something that was wandering by. <br /> <br />Try to scout out areas first so that you know where most of the wanders are before you pull, a wandering monster can turn an easy fight into a slaughter. <br /> <br />And Finally at the higher levels when monsters remember they are mad at you when you stand up, splitting a spawn becomes more of a challenge, cause what you're wanting to try and do then is to let 1 or more MOBs get back to thier spawn point (90% chance forget rate) and let the target MOB come back to you alone. <br /> <br />There is another Aspect of Feign Pulling that should only be done it groups that work well together.  This is having a secondary puller tag a target mob and finish pulling it back to the group, here's how it works. <br /> <br />1) This technique will require a pretty good chunk of space to maneuver in so It's best used in area's where you do long pulls and the chance of wandering mobs is very minimal. <br /> <br />2) This technique will work with a tank as the secondary puller, though another monk is the best choice, because of the ability to abort if something goes wrong. <br /> <br />3) The Primary Puller goes out and tags a mob and pulls several back to a point and feigns.  (It is usually best to have a pre-arranged location to feign at so the 2nd puller won't be aggroed accidentally). <br /> <br />4) The best situation is that the mobs will start to wander back at different times.  The 2nd puller then tags (usually the last mob to wander back) his mob and pulls it back.  If this is done properly, all the other mobs will be out of aggro range of the 2nd puller and his target mob.  He can then pull it back to the main group. <br /> <br />The down side to this is that your primary puller will most likely have to stay Feigned through most of the fight to let the other mobs get back to thier starting locations without coming back after him when he stands up. <br /> <br />This last type of pulling is one that is used quite extensively on High Level Raids where a single Mob can be hard to handle. <br /> <br />Side Note)  Please people, if you're going to pull, learn how to vector (running straight ahead and sideways at the same time).  With most normal mobs, this will keep you far enough ahead of them so that they can't attack you.  Which means once you get back, the cleric has to waste less mana and won't be immediately aggroed by healing you.</p>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >2 replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
