<p>some other tricks i use: <br /> <br />1. using walls with casters mobs.  <br /> <br />IE run behind a wall ( easy to find a wall in dungeon )  <br />wait first casting  <br />you know then that the mob will need to have you in sight before re casting on you.. so FD after 1st cast.  <br /> <br />Handy to split caster / warrior mobs. <br /> <br /> <br />2. 2 mnks pulling. <br />i'm playing a lot the back puller. It means FDing on a safe spot far enough from the group while the main puller pulls. If main puller bring like 6 7 mobs on my fd spot, i watch an occasion to pull one.( IE RZ raid, how to split boss from the 7 8 fake boss ) . <br />PS : i'm lazy so i dont mind fding all the time and sometimes saying to raid / group inc bad moffo ;p.  <br /> <br /> <br />3. ping pong FD. <br />You got 2 mobs... agro one enough so he follows you, let the tank agro the other one, then flee far from the group. <br />FD... naturally the mob will come back to the group. wait FD refresh, wake up. if the mob did not forgot you he will run to you ( it is rare he will forget you if you dmged him ;p ). so you ping pong the add with the group. <br /> <br /> <br />4 bioluminescent orb. <br />hell this one is quite dangerous to use and works like 40% of the time. And not on all mobs. <br />The effect of bio orb is to blind mobs . mob is blind, it means mob will attack nearest player. But if no player is near the mob will turn his back and flee.  <br />2 mobs, you use bio orb on the first, the first mob will flee, the second mob will follow you to camp. <br />FD.  <br />and voila. <br /> <br />Point is that in dungeons the blind mob will run randomly in the dungeon and will bring friends with him. nice way to start a train too. ( so be sure to have the msg your ennemies has forgotten you if you are not sure ) . <br /> <br />Cherub. <br /> <br />PS: nice post here, really complete, i like it.  <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Mon Jun 21 16:56:17 2004 by Gaellian</span></i></p>
